<subSubSection box="[151,522,1590,1617]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,522,1590,1617]" box="[151,522,1590,1617]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,522,1590,1617]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,522,1590,1617]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[207,311,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[207,311,1591,1617]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
generic complex
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="443" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1663,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
Male genitalia of the generic complex are characterized by the simple valva gradually tapering distally and lacking a corona and a costal process which are present in genera of the ‘ 
<emphasis box="[891,1036,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
<taxonomicName box="[891,1006,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Agrochola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Agrochola</taxonomicName>
—
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Warren" authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1910" box="[1035,1203,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Telorta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1035,1112,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Telorta</emphasis>
Warren
</taxonomicName>
— 
<taxonomicName authority="Warren" authorityName="Warren" box="[1231,1437,1699,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyalobole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1231,1348,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Hyalobole</emphasis>
Warren
</taxonomicName>
generic complex’. In female genitalia, the well-developed antrum separated from the posterior section of the ductus bursae by a membranous section is characteristic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="444" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1663,2013]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,465]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="444" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
<bibRefCitation author="Ronkay, L. &amp; Yela, J. L. &amp; Hreblay, M." box="[199,440,1807,1833]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" refId="ref7969" refString="Ronkay, L., Yela, J. L. &amp; Hreblay, M. (2001) Hadeninae II. Noctuidae Europaeae. Vol. 5. Entomological Press, Soro, 352 pp." type="book" year="2001">
Ronkay 
<emphasis box="[296,355,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">et al.</emphasis>
(2001)
</bibRefCitation>
considered the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[700,798,1807,1833]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[700,798,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a member of the ‘ 
<emphasis box="[1052,1277,1807,1833]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Agrochola-Conistra</emphasis>
generic complex’ comprising numerous genera in Eurasia and North America. Subsequently, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ronkay, L. &amp; Ronkay, G. &amp; Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z." box="[1059,1291,1843,1869]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" refId="ref7916" refString="Ronkay, L., Ronkay, G., Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z. (2017) Xyleninae I. The Agrochola generic complex. A Taxonomic Atlas of the Eurasian and North African Noctuoidea. Vol. 9. Heterocera Press, Budapest, 342 pp." type="book" year="2017">
Ronkay 
<emphasis box="[1153,1210,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
separated so called ‘conistroid’ genera (called here as the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[653,751,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[653,751,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
generic complex) from the ‘ 
<emphasis box="[1073,1436,1879,1905]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">
<taxonomicName box="[1073,1188,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Agrochola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Agrochola</taxonomicName>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1910" box="[1216,1293,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Telorta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Telorta</taxonomicName>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[1322,1436,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyalobole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hyalobole</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
generic complex’. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ronkay, L. &amp; Yela, J. L. &amp; Hreblay, M." box="[367,610,1915,1941]" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" refId="ref7969" refString="Ronkay, L., Yela, J. L. &amp; Hreblay, M. (2001) Hadeninae II. Noctuidae Europaeae. Vol. 5. Entomological Press, Soro, 352 pp." type="book" year="2001">
Ronkay 
<emphasis box="[465,525,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">et al.</emphasis>
(2001)
</bibRefCitation>
listed such Nearctic genera as 
<taxonomicName authority="Franclemont" authorityName="Franclemont" authorityYear="1937" box="[977,1279,1915,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Metaxaglaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[977,1123,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Metaxaglaea</emphasis>
Franclemont
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Franclemont" authorityName="Franclemont" authorityYear="1943" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Chaetaglaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1293,1436,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Chaetaglaea</emphasis>
Franclemont
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Grote" authorityName="Grote" authorityYear="1878" box="[349,523,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Epiglaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[349,450,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Epiglaea</emphasis>
Grote
</taxonomicName>
as closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[764,862,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[764,862,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the male genitalia ground plan of these taxa is significantly different from that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[628,726,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[628,726,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and closer to such 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1837" box="[946,1049,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Xylenina">Xylenina</taxonomicName>
genera as 
<taxonomicName authority="Snellen" authorityName="Snellen" authorityYear="1867" box="[1171,1362,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Spudaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1171,1267,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Spudaea</emphasis>
Snellen
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1818" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Jodia" kingdom="Animalia" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="444" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="443" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1374,1436,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="443">Jodia</emphasis>
Hübner
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Reisser" authorityName="Reisser" authorityYear="1930" box="[249,402,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Evisa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[249,311,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Evisa</emphasis>
Reisser
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner. Besides" authorityName="Hubner. Besides" box="[460,746,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eupsilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[460,553,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Eupsilia</emphasis>
Hübner. Besides
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[755,853,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[755,853,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, we include in the generic complex the genus 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Suginistra</emphasis>
L. Ronkay, G. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ronkay, L. &amp; Ronkay, G. &amp; Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z." box="[400,749,187,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" refId="ref7916" refString="Ronkay, L., Ronkay, G., Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z. (2017) Xyleninae I. The Agrochola generic complex. A Taxonomic Atlas of the Eurasian and North African Noctuoidea. Vol. 9. Heterocera Press, Budapest, 342 pp." type="book" year="2017">Ronkay, Gyulai &amp; Varga, 2017</bibRefCitation>
which was considered by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ronkay, L. &amp; Ronkay, G. &amp; Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z." box="[1050,1285,187,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" refId="ref7916" refString="Ronkay, L., Ronkay, G., Gyulai, P. &amp; Varga, Z. (2017) Xyleninae I. The Agrochola generic complex. A Taxonomic Atlas of the Eurasian and North African Noctuoidea. Vol. 9. Heterocera Press, Budapest, 342 pp." type="book" year="2017">
Ronkay 
<emphasis box="[1145,1203,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
as a member of the 
<emphasis box="[224,556,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Agrochola-Telorta-Hyalobole</emphasis>
generic complex due to its external similarity to 
<taxonomicName box="[1114,1231,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Agrochola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1114,1231,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Agrochola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its allies, and three additional new genera described below. Nevertheless, it is worth mentioning that the subdivision of genera into ‘generic complexes’ as well as evaluation of their relationships based only on morphological features is quite subjective and artificial. 
<emphasis box="[433,548,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Suginistra</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth, 2022" authorityName="Benedek &amp; Volynkin &amp; Saldaitis &amp; Tóth" authorityYear="2022" box="[606,726,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Vargalorta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. n.">
<emphasis box="[606,726,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Vargalorta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[734,815,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[734,815,331,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" rank="genus">gen. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are probably transitional groups between the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1821" box="[1338,1436,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Conistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1338,1436,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">Conistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[201,565,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="444">
<taxonomicName box="[201,316,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Agrochola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Agrochola</taxonomicName>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Warren" authorityYear="1910" box="[345,422,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Telorta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Telorta</taxonomicName>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[451,565,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyalobole" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="444" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hyalobole</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
‘generic complexes’. The question on relationships between the genera and their status can be clarified by using molecular methods with numerous Palaearctic, Oriental and Nearctic groups included in the analysis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
